The `isPowerOfThree` function calculates the base-3 logarithm of the input number `n`. If `n` is a power of three, this value should be an integer. By checking if the integer part of the log value equals the log value itself, we can determine whether `n` is a power of three.

Note: The `Math.log()` function computes natural logarithms (logarithms base e), so we divide by `Math.log(3)` to compute the base-3 logarithm. Also, because floating-point precision issues can cause slight inaccuracies, the comparison uses `Math.floor(logValue) == logValue` instead of `logValue == (int)logValue` to accurately check if the log value is an integer.

